<br>
Bravo to your 8th shawl ! I am the step just before, all Imbued Royal Armor done, and chat with the Dain, getting the Issue Kit done - so ready for the Final Kombat ...<br>
<br>
May I ask you what speficic problems/difficulties I must be aware of when recruiting my guildies for the triggered event when I will have given the orders to General Bragmur ? What did you notice of things to be aware while you fought all the waves ?<br>
<br>
And, for the fun, a little story about summoning the Dain : as I went into IK, the King was not up, so I spoke to Chamberlain and he &quot;summoned&quot; the Dain.<br>
<br>
And I saw him casting  and could see messages in my chat bar &quot;Dain Frostreaver IV has become more etc etc&quot; - BUT no Dain ! Could not see him ! Neither on his throne, nor in his bedroom, so WTF, wondered I !<br>
<br>
Well, after a couple of minutes of sincere panic, I just pitched up - Dain was not sitting ON his throne, but ABOVE it --- so look up and you might see the Dain ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmatelemental>XalmatElemental</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 2:07:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 8th Shawl at Last!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>May I ask you what speficic problems/difficulties I must be aware of when recruiting my guildies for the triggered event when I will have given the orders to General Bragmur ? What did you notice of things to be aware while you fought all the waves ?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To start, you need three solid groups to be effective. Four is overkill. Make sure you're tank heavy, since the giants can't be mezzed. The wolves are mezzable.<br>
<br>
You will need a CC crew to keep the General busy. I used a monk and enchanter. Once each wave started, the monk would aggro the general and kite him around. Once the wave is down, we'd med up, and once ready the enchanter would mem blur and we'd be on our way. Of course, the general also decided to attack our helpless bards with their AE mana song. After the fourth wave my bards called the ping-pong aggro from their songs &quot;Passing the Dwarf&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you have peeps KOS to the Coldain, they need to stay as far away from the General as possible. But if they do get aggro from the General, they need to ignore it, and you need to call Mem Blur.<br>
<br>
Make absolutely sure NO ONE attacks the General other than your CC crew. If they get aggro, tell them to not fight back. If they have a pet and get aggro, they must /pet hold, or /pet get lost.<br>
<br>
The actual fights aren't too hard. If your guild can easily handle the Kael Arena, this is a cakewalk. Make sure your MA attacks each &quot;Commander&quot; giant that spawns. Those are higher level, and do summon. The rest don't.<br>
<br>
What I did was delegate a MA, and several CC tanks. The MA would call primary target, and the CC tanks kept the additional giants busy. Casters and anyone not CCing should go off the MA at all times.<br>
<br>
The general moves slow. I mean slow. The el-cheapo horse is faster than him. So this gives you plenty of time to move ahead and take out any annoying greenies you find.<br>
<br>
Should about cover it. Happy trails. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=adonhiram>Adonhiram</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 6:25:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 8th Shawl at Last!</span><hr size=1> Thank you very much ! Will soon call my guild :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showPrevMessage?topicID=1248.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showNextMessage?topicID=1248.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1248.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.threadControl?topicID=1248.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1248.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1248.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><